The progress of science and technology at the end of the XIXth and first half of 
the XXth century paved the way to start space exploration by humanity. The 
flight of Yu. A. Gagarin on April 12, 1961 was one of the history watersheds 
that had a great many of social implications. Piloted missions to space 
