Current literature indicates that elevated IL-6 serum levels are associated with 
diseases, disability and mortality in the elderly. In this paper, we studied the 
IL-6 promoter genetic variability at -174 C/G locus and its effect on IL-6 serum 
levels in a total of 700 people from 60 to 110 years of age, including 323 
