The chronic effect of linear alkylbenzene sulfonate (LAS12) on a daphnid species 
(Daphnia galeata) was examined by the life table experiment. The estimated 
responses in the intrinsic rate of population growth r were analyzed with two 
alternate concentration-response functions, i.e., the power function and the 
quadratic function. Based on the best-fit power function model with biases 
