defined as the concentration of chemicals that reduces the population growth 
rate (the intrinsic rate of natural increase) by 50%, was estimated as 2.5 mg/L. 
The 48-h acute immobility test yielded EC50 of 4.6 mg/L. The population-level 
effect of LAS12 on this test species is considerably more sensitive than the 
acute lethal effects to neonates.

